*
ANOVA = One-way ANOVA variance analysis. *
Tukey = Test of Tukey, 1–2 comparing the age-groups 1 = the youth, 2 = the middle-aged; 1–3 comparing the age-groups 1 = the youth, 3 = the older generation; 2–3 comparing the age-groups 2 = the middle-aged, 3 = the older generation. *
K-W = Kruskall-Wallis variance analysis made in the cases were the requirements for the One-way ANOVA variance analysis are not fulfilled according to the test of homogeneity of variances. *
K-W pairwise comparison = Pairwise comparisons made by the method of Siegel and Castellan from the foundations of Kruskall-Wallis variance analysis, 1–2 comparing the age-groups 1 = the youth, 2 = the middle-aged; 1–3 comparing the age-groups 1 = the youth, 3 = the older generation; 2–3 comparing the age-groups 2 = the middle-aged, 3 = the older generation.
The values for statistical significance are p < .001 = very significant; p < .01 = significant; p < .05 = less significant.
